WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:09.958
Support Admin Watch on
kissasia.cam or kisskh.org

00:10.708 --> 00:12.708
♪♪

00:14.250 --> 00:15.583
[Vault door clanking]

00:17.083 --> 00:18.875
Stop! Lucy!

00:20.000 --> 00:21.416
[Lucy MacLean]
I'm looking for my father.

00:22.125 --> 00:23.916
You are my world.

00:24.791 --> 00:27.375
[Lucy] He was kidnapped
by this woman named Moldaver.

00:27.458 --> 00:28.916
[Wilzig] You need to go home.

00:29.000 --> 00:31.541
Vault Dwellers are
an endangered species here.

00:32.540 --> 00:35.250
You come from a world of rules, of laws.

00:35.291 --> 00:38.541
This place is indifferent to all of that.

00:39.041 --> 00:40.625
I'm not going back without my dad.

00:40.708 --> 00:43.000
Then you will have to adapt.

00:44.708 --> 00:46.833
[Honcho]
A bounty came down.

00:46.916 --> 00:50.375
Somebody made a run...
from the Enclave.

00:51.791 --> 00:54.958
[Quintus]
This target has with him an object

00:55.041 --> 00:58.750
of profound potential

00:58.833 --> 01:00.458
to harm our nation

01:02.708 --> 01:04.375
or to save it.

01:04.750 --> 01:06.375
[cocking gun]

01:07.375 --> 01:10.000
-[Ghoul] Where is it?
-[Lucy] You can't treat people like this!

01:10.583 --> 01:11.625
[screaming]

01:12.000 --> 01:13.041
[Ghoul]
Yeah? Why's that?

01:14.916 --> 01:16.583
Because of the golden rule.

01:17.583 --> 01:20.333
"Do unto others as you would have
done unto you."

01:23.250 --> 01:25.000
What are you?

01:25.666 --> 01:27.666
Oh, I'm you, sweetie.

01:27.750 --> 01:30.208
♪♪

01:35.458 --> 01:38.541
You just give it a little time.

01:40.833 --> 01:43.375
[Kate Williams] Vault-Tec
is the largest company in America.

01:43.458 --> 01:46.208
There’s a lot of money in selling
the end of the world.

01:46.541 --> 01:48.666
-[Cooper] What is it?
-[Kate] It's a listening device.

01:48.750 --> 01:50.333
You want me to spy on my wife?

01:50.416 --> 01:52.791
[Barb] I will do whatever it takes
to make sure the people I love--

01:52.875 --> 01:54.833
that is you and that is Janey--

01:54.916 --> 01:58.666
go into a special Vault
for management.

02:00.125 --> 02:02.875
[Kate] America has been locked
in a resource war.

02:02.958 --> 02:05.458
Vault-Tec bought the means
to end that war.

02:05.541 --> 02:08.500
Cold Fusion. Infinite energy.

02:10.250 --> 02:11.708
-Whoo.
-[device beeps]

02:12.541 --> 02:14.666
[Barb]
A nuclear event would be a tragedy.

02:14.750 --> 02:16.458
But also an opportunity.

02:17.375 --> 02:19.541
Because war, well...

02:21.791 --> 02:23.500
war never changes.

02:25.375 --> 02:27.291
♪♪

02:29.291 --> 02:30.625
The water chip is destroyed.

02:30.708 --> 02:34.083
The Vault only has enough water to keep
our population alive for two months.

02:34.166 --> 02:36.666
[Betty]
We are the lucky ones.

02:36.750 --> 02:40.250
Three Vaults separated to prevent
the spread of threats.

02:40.333 --> 02:43.875
You don't think it's weird that we
always elect an Overseer from Vault 31?

02:43.958 --> 02:45.625
Steph's from Vault 31.

02:48.208 --> 02:52.125
[Betty] Some of us will be moving
into Vault 32 to start anew.

02:57.791 --> 03:00.166
[Norm]
Is this where my dad's from?

03:02.000 --> 03:04.250
[Bud Askins/Brain-on-a-Roomba]
These are Bud's Buds.

03:04.333 --> 03:06.500
My Buds.
A well-trained staff

03:06.583 --> 03:08.458
of highly supervised junior executives

03:08.541 --> 03:10.416
from my own assistant training program.

03:12.166 --> 03:15.208
Because the future of humanity
comes down to one word:

03:15.916 --> 03:17.291
management.

03:17.375 --> 03:18.833
You know,
I actually have to get back home.

03:23.833 --> 03:25.958
My name isn't Titus.
It's Maximus.

03:26.333 --> 03:29.625
Titus is the name of the Knight
who owned this suit before me.

03:29.708 --> 03:30.708
[roaring]

03:32.833 --> 03:34.291
[Lucy]
You're a good person.

03:34.541 --> 03:36.208
The Wasteland sucks.

03:39.458 --> 03:41.083
[Maximus]
The Brotherhood.

03:42.958 --> 03:44.875
They're never gonna
stop looking for the artifact.

03:49.458 --> 03:51.000
Find me.

03:52.583 --> 03:54.500
I will.

03:54.583 --> 03:56.583
♪♪

04:03.250 --> 04:05.166
Give me my dad back.

04:05.666 --> 04:07.458
But first...

04:08.500 --> 04:11.041
what if I tell you who he really is?

04:12.208 --> 04:14.500
Shady Sands.

04:15.208 --> 04:18.457
Your father burned that city
to the ground.

04:21.375 --> 04:23.332
I wonder if anyone survived.

04:23.416 --> 04:25.832
♪♪

04:25.916 --> 04:27.375
[Maximus] I did.

04:29.707 --> 04:32.457
[Hank] If the problem
with the world is factions,

04:32.541 --> 04:35.250
endlessly fighting,
endlessly at war,

04:35.332 --> 04:39.207
then what is the solution
but to get rid of the factions?

04:39.291 --> 04:42.041
To make the world us,

04:42.125 --> 04:44.082
only ours to shape.

04:51.625 --> 04:53.375
[Hank]
You see what this place does to people?

04:56.875 --> 04:59.457
Now I've waited over 200 years

05:00.083 --> 05:03.541
to ask somebody one question.

05:05.000 --> 05:07.541
Where's my fuckin' family?

05:14.208 --> 05:17.000
It's easier to track a stuck pig

05:17.082 --> 05:19.375
than to ask it where it's off to.

05:21.666 --> 05:23.166
Now you can stay here

05:23.250 --> 05:25.875
or you could come meet your makers.

05:25.957 --> 05:27.957
♪♪

05:33.916 --> 05:35.457
Okey-dokey.

05:38.582 --> 05:40.457
[troops]
All hail Knight Maximus!

05:40.916 --> 05:42.791
All hail Knight Maximus!

05:42.875 --> 05:45.000
All hail Knight Maximus!

05:45.082 --> 05:46.791
All hail Knight Maximus!

05:47.625 --> 05:50.000
[Ghoul]
You look out at this Wasteland,

05:50.082 --> 05:51.666
looks like chaos.

05:54.082 --> 05:56.207
But there’s always somebody
behind the wheel.

06:11.041 --> 06:14.041
[♪ Peggy Lee: "Cheek to Cheek"]

06:24.250 --> 06:25.375
♪ Heaven ♪

06:26.666 --> 06:28.582
♪ I'm in heaven ♪

06:30.875 --> 06:33.166
[Mr. Handy]
Could I help you have a better day?

06:33.250 --> 06:34.957
♪ And my heart beats so
that I can hardly speak ♪

06:35.041 --> 06:36.791
[crowd shouting]

06:36.875 --> 06:39.207
♪ And I seem to find...

06:39.291 --> 06:42.375
[Robert House] Look, our primary concern
at RobCo Industries

06:42.457 --> 06:45.666
is creating greater efficiency
in the workplace.

06:45.750 --> 06:48.125
If the American government
needs a hand

06:48.207 --> 06:51.416
in settling our more
international disputes...

06:52.791 --> 06:54.250
well they know who to call.

06:54.332 --> 06:56.332
[Bill]
Goddamn parasite is what he is.

06:57.582 --> 06:59.250
We didn't vote for this dumb maggot.

07:00.083 --> 07:01.875
[stranger]
Oh, yes we did.

07:03.541 --> 07:05.541
-[pool balls clacking]
-[lighter flicking]

07:10.541 --> 07:12.958
Every dollar spent is a vote cast.

07:13.875 --> 07:17.332
And that fellow right there,
he has more votes

07:17.416 --> 07:20.707
than every one of those
pan-headed politicians in Washington.

07:23.207 --> 07:25.082
You his biggest fan or somethin'?

07:26.332 --> 07:28.332
[tense music playing]

07:29.416 --> 07:30.541
Why yes.

07:31.666 --> 07:33.166
Yes, I believe I am.

07:35.375 --> 07:37.957
And if the will of the American people
was to endow that man

07:38.041 --> 07:41.457
with a significant portion
of its wealth, well...

07:41.541 --> 07:43.916
well, good golly,
that can't be a bad thing now, can it?

07:45.707 --> 07:47.916
What trade are you in, friend?

07:50.041 --> 07:51.207
Construction.

07:52.125 --> 07:55.500
Ah. So you must use
the H&H Nail Gun.

07:56.541 --> 07:58.125
It's a marvelous machine.

07:59.207 --> 08:02.166
Nice in the hands,
smooth action.

08:02.250 --> 08:04.458
Sure beats using a silly old hammer,
doesn't it?

08:05.750 --> 08:07.416
Why, I thought you'd be grateful.

08:09.041 --> 08:10.583
"Grateful." [chuckles]

08:11.750 --> 08:13.500
I think you're in the wrong bar, pal.

08:15.291 --> 08:18.291
Hmm, obsolescence.

08:18.375 --> 08:21.166
[clicking tongue]
It's a heck of a thing.

08:22.291 --> 08:24.375
You know, I try and see it
from your perspective,

08:24.457 --> 08:27.457
but it's hard to imagine being so dim

08:27.541 --> 08:30.041
as to be caught off guard
by the inevitable.

08:32.040 --> 08:33.165
[grunting]

08:34.165 --> 08:36.000
[stranger]
Ah... Ah!

08:39.040 --> 08:41.040
Hit me in the mouth.

08:41.125 --> 08:42.332
I think I'd enjoy it.

08:43.250 --> 08:44.250
[grunting]

08:44.333 --> 08:46.790
-[wheezing, groaning]
-[men laughing]

08:50.665 --> 08:54.290
I'm rarely wrong, but let's move on.

08:55.915 --> 08:57.458
[button clicking]

09:03.875 --> 09:08.375
That is $31 million.

09:12.000 --> 09:16.791
Now, what would you do
for all of that money?

09:19.958 --> 09:21.125
Short of ideas?

09:22.125 --> 09:25.083
Well, that's no surprise.
How 'bout I offer you one?

09:28.958 --> 09:30.583
[objects rustling]

09:34.915 --> 09:37.333
Allow me to put this...

09:37.415 --> 09:38.750
on the back of your neck.

09:40.125 --> 09:41.708
What the hell is it?

09:42.790 --> 09:47.415
Oh, just call it good old-fashioned
market research.

09:48.208 --> 09:51.040
All I'm asking you to do
is to insert this

09:51.125 --> 09:52.665
into the back of your neck,

09:52.750 --> 09:55.625
and all that nice money
right there is yours.

09:57.208 --> 09:59.625
How about I break those hands
you've never used?

09:59.708 --> 10:01.708
-See if you even notice.
-[laughing]

10:01.791 --> 10:03.416
Then we'll take his money.

10:03.500 --> 10:05.708
-These fucking rich people are so--
-Eh, well...

10:06.416 --> 10:08.083
[gasping]

10:09.208 --> 10:11.458
[grunting]

10:11.541 --> 10:14.416
[high-pitched ringing]

10:14.500 --> 10:16.208
[ringing stops]

10:25.375 --> 10:27.625
I'd like for you
to do me a small favor.

10:28.166 --> 10:29.333
[Black Box activates]

10:29.416 --> 10:30.708
Get rid of your friends.

10:36.290 --> 10:37.790
[Bill's friend] Bill.

10:37.875 --> 10:39.540
Bill. Oh!

10:39.625 --> 10:40.625
Ooh!

10:41.500 --> 10:42.625
Ooh!

10:43.665 --> 10:46.500
Oh, you fellows
do use the H&H Nail Gun!

10:47.125 --> 10:48.540
[loud thudding]

10:48.625 --> 10:49.875
You should feel good about it.

10:50.833 --> 10:52.625
You paid for all of this!

10:58.333 --> 11:00.583
-[bat cracking, clattering]
-[stranger chuckles]

11:05.666 --> 11:06.916
[dial turns]

11:12.750 --> 11:14.916
-[dial turns]
-[Black Box sound intensifies]

11:16.041 --> 11:18.666
[dramatic music playing]

11:22.916 --> 11:24.125
[body thuds]

11:25.958 --> 11:27.708
[squelches]

11:32.415 --> 11:34.625
♪ Heaven ♪

11:34.708 --> 11:37.790
♪ Ooh, I'm in heaven ♪

11:37.875 --> 11:42.833
The world may end,
but progress marches on.

11:44.833 --> 11:49.875
♪ And I seem to find
the happiness I seek ♪

11:52.000 --> 11:56.500
♪ When we're out together
dancing cheek to cheek ♪♪

11:58.750 --> 12:00.750
♪♪

12:06.666 --> 12:08.208
[Nick The Prick] Khans!

12:09.041 --> 12:11.916
I got something real exciting
for you today.

12:15.250 --> 12:17.250
[inhaler hissing]

12:18.541 --> 12:20.791
This asshole
has been tormentin' us Khans

12:20.875 --> 12:22.833
since before your granddaddies
were born.

12:23.541 --> 12:24.916
And today!

12:25.000 --> 12:27.041
[chuckles]

12:27.125 --> 12:31.125
Some little bounty hunter
put him right in our fuckin' laps.

12:31.208 --> 12:33.208
So, now we settle the score!

12:35.583 --> 12:37.415
How do you feel about that?

12:38.125 --> 12:41.125
[ominous music playing]

12:51.208 --> 12:52.875
Didn't that used to be a store?

12:54.833 --> 12:58.750
I think I bought a soda pop there
'bout 25 years back.

12:58.833 --> 13:01.250
Are you about fuckin' done?

13:01.333 --> 13:03.000
We got some justice to--

13:03.083 --> 13:06.375
Darla! Yeah, woman behind the counter,
her name was Darla.

13:06.458 --> 13:08.958
She was a reasonable woman

13:10.416 --> 13:13.416
'til you matching-jacket motherfuckers
had to move in.

13:15.833 --> 13:19.625
Well, it's been nice chattin' with y'all,
but if it's okay with you...

13:20.625 --> 13:22.291
I'm about ready to get on with it.

13:24.333 --> 13:26.041
What, you can't hear me?

13:26.125 --> 13:27.750
I'll say it louder.
I said...

13:28.666 --> 13:30.750
I'm about ready to get on with it.

13:31.541 --> 13:33.333
[vocalist yodeling]

13:37.540 --> 13:39.458
To get on with it!

13:46.083 --> 13:47.083
Fuck.

13:47.750 --> 13:49.290
[grunting]

13:49.375 --> 13:51.000
[rope creaking]

13:51.083 --> 13:52.833
-[Ghoul choking]
-[Nick laughing]

13:53.583 --> 13:54.833
[sighs]

13:54.915 --> 13:57.458
[laughter continues]

13:57.540 --> 13:59.375
-Well, you--
-[Lucy MacLean] Hi, excuse me.

13:59.458 --> 14:00.458
Hi.

14:00.541 --> 14:02.541
'Scuse me.
So sorry.

14:02.625 --> 14:04.250
I'm hoping you can settle
an argument

14:04.333 --> 14:06.833
between myself
and my traveling companion there.

14:06.916 --> 14:10.750
We are hunting down my father,
who is not a good guy.

14:10.833 --> 14:13.875
And on this journey, we found ourselves
in need of food and supplies.

14:13.958 --> 14:16.958
Plan A was to leave you alone
and avoid this scenario altogether,

14:17.041 --> 14:19.916
but we've tried that,
and I'd just start starving to death.

14:20.000 --> 14:21.250
-[chuckles]
-[choking]

14:21.333 --> 14:24.416
Plan B-- his idea, by the way--
was for me to turn him over to you

14:24.500 --> 14:26.041
so that you would open up your safe
and give me

14:26.125 --> 14:27.750
the considerable bounty
you put out on him.

14:27.833 --> 14:30.416
-Fucking shoot!
-The idea was I would shoot him down,

14:30.500 --> 14:31.916
he'd take your weapons,

14:32.000 --> 14:34.833
and use whatever violence necessary
in order for us to escape.

14:34.915 --> 14:37.583
Which, in my experience thus far is...

14:38.500 --> 14:40.625
it's a lot of violence, so...

14:41.915 --> 14:44.125
I'm really, really hoping
you'll agree to Plan C?

14:46.415 --> 14:47.750
What's Plan C?

14:48.750 --> 14:50.290
[choking]

14:50.375 --> 14:51.958
You just let us go.

14:53.583 --> 14:55.000
And we keep the caps you gave me,

14:55.083 --> 14:58.125
which to be clear,
we do need for our survival.

15:01.875 --> 15:04.250
And just to ask the question,
would it help if I said "please"?

15:08.000 --> 15:10.750
Whoever kills the girl
gets to eat the dog.

15:10.833 --> 15:12.250
[men cheering]

15:12.333 --> 15:14.000
Okey-dokey!

15:14.083 --> 15:15.083
[gunshot]

15:15.166 --> 15:17.041
[vocalist yodeling]

15:17.458 --> 15:19.250
-[gunfire]
-[Dogmeat whimpering]

15:20.291 --> 15:21.708
Ah, jeez.

15:21.791 --> 15:23.791
-[gunfire continues]
-[grunting]

15:29.500 --> 15:30.916
Ah, fuck!

15:39.540 --> 15:41.208
Fucking amateur.

15:55.833 --> 15:58.665
[♪ Marty Robbins: "Big Iron"]

16:01.708 --> 16:06.666
♪ To the town of Agua Fria
rode a stranger one fine day ♪

16:08.000 --> 16:10.166
♪ Hardly spoke to folks
around him ♪

16:10.250 --> 16:12.791
-♪ Didn't have too much to say ♪
-[gun clicking]

16:12.875 --> 16:14.125
[Dogmeat barking]

16:14.208 --> 16:17.833
♪ No one dared to ask his business,
no one dared to make a slip ♪

16:17.916 --> 16:20.541
-[gunfire continues]
-♪ The stranger there among them ♪

16:20.625 --> 16:25.333
♪ Had a big iron on his hip,
big iron on his hip ♪

16:27.666 --> 16:32.375
♪ It was early in the morning
when he rode into the town ♪

16:33.958 --> 16:38.875
♪ He came riding from the south side,
slowly looking all around ♪

16:39.790 --> 16:43.750
♪ "He's an outlaw loose and running,"
came the whisper from each lip ♪

16:43.833 --> 16:46.500
-♪ And he's here to do some business ♪
-[grunts]

16:46.583 --> 16:48.958
-♪ With the big iron on his hip ♪
-[body splattering]

16:49.040 --> 16:52.833
♪ Big iron, big iron ♪

16:52.915 --> 16:57.250
♪ When he tried to match the Ranger
with the big iron on his hip ♪

16:57.333 --> 17:04.208
♪ Big iron on his hip ♪♪

17:10.500 --> 17:12.125
[neon sign buzzing]

17:12.208 --> 17:15.915
-[wind blowing]
-[Dogmeat barking]

17:16.000 --> 17:17.915
[Ghoul] I know you think
you being helpful...

17:18.750 --> 17:21.333
shootin' folks in the kneecaps
and the ass.

17:22.540 --> 17:24.500
But if I'm being honest, you ain't.

17:24.583 --> 17:27.375
I'm not gonna apologize
for not murdering people.

17:31.375 --> 17:36.125
[sighs] Well all that matters to me
is you shoot that fuckin' rope.

17:37.333 --> 17:40.333
♪♪

17:44.000 --> 17:45.416
Well, I did, didn't I?

17:47.208 --> 17:50.208
[ominous music playing]

18:26.000 --> 18:27.125
[Lucy gasps softly]

18:28.125 --> 18:30.500
Still looks like all the old photos.

18:33.750 --> 18:35.333
Bombs got shot down.

18:36.583 --> 18:38.291
Most of 'em, anyway.

18:42.000 --> 18:43.666
Well, if they could do that
for Las Vegas,

18:43.750 --> 18:45.875
why couldn't they just do that
for America?

18:47.500 --> 18:49.833
Because there was no "they."

18:49.916 --> 18:52.083
There was a "him."

18:52.166 --> 18:54.333
A man by the name
of Robert House.

18:55.833 --> 18:58.416
Maybe that's where your family went.
They're safe there.

18:59.791 --> 19:01.625
Nowhere near Robert House is safe.

19:07.791 --> 19:09.708
Why would my dad
go to Las Vegas?

19:13.583 --> 19:14.958
[Ghoul sighs]

19:21.375 --> 19:24.375
[ominous music playing]

19:39.750 --> 19:41.375
[Robert] [over listening device]
There's a lot of earning potential

19:41.458 --> 19:42.583
with the end of the world.

19:49.791 --> 19:52.041
How can you guarantee results?

19:54.708 --> 19:57.166
[voice echoing]
By dropping the bomb ourselves.

19:59.000 --> 20:02.000
[high-pitched ringing,
music swells]

20:05.125 --> 20:07.291
Janey? Honey?

20:07.375 --> 20:08.625
-Janey!
-Daddy.

20:08.708 --> 20:11.083
-Hey. Hey.
-Daddy.

20:15.416 --> 20:17.125
Listen to me.

20:17.208 --> 20:19.375
I want you to go to your room, okay?

20:19.458 --> 20:22.166
And I want you to pick out
your three favorite outfits

20:22.250 --> 20:24.583
and your favorite toy, okay?

20:24.666 --> 20:26.166
And then meet me back here.

20:27.875 --> 20:29.166
Okay, go.

20:33.000 --> 20:34.291
[sighs]

20:37.708 --> 20:38.750
[♪ Eddy Arnold: "Make the World Go Away"]

20:38.833 --> 20:42.291
♪ Make the world go away ♪

20:44.416 --> 20:49.291
♪ And get it off my shoulders ♪

20:51.875 --> 20:54.750
♪ Say the things you used to say...

20:54.833 --> 20:56.083
Where are we going, Daddy?

20:58.500 --> 21:02.208
♪ And make the world go away ♪

21:02.291 --> 21:03.416
Bakersfield.

21:03.500 --> 21:06.208
Um, we're gonna go to Bakersfield,
sweetie, okay?

21:07.916 --> 21:09.375
What about Mommy?

21:10.333 --> 21:12.291
-Is she coming with us?
-[announcer] [on radio] Please be advised,

21:12.375 --> 21:14.416
the test of the Civil Alert
Broadcast System...

21:14.500 --> 21:15.833
-[volume increasing]
-...for Los Angeles County

21:15.916 --> 21:17.541
-will commence in 10 seconds.
-[bicycle bell ringing]

21:21.416 --> 21:23.458
[Cooper Howard] Come on, come on,
come on, come on, come on, come on.

21:23.541 --> 21:25.291
[tires screeching]

21:26.125 --> 21:27.416
[sighs]

21:27.500 --> 21:31.458
♪ And make the world go away ♪

21:33.833 --> 21:39.083
♪ Make the world go away ♪

21:39.166 --> 21:42.375
[alarms blaring]

21:42.458 --> 21:44.541
[panicked chatter]

21:47.416 --> 21:49.416
-[man on the street] Get inside!
-[alarms continue blaring]

21:51.333 --> 21:53.916
[announcer] [on radio]
Commencing test. Repeat...

21:54.000 --> 21:55.583
This is a test.

21:55.666 --> 21:56.916
It's just a test!

21:57.000 --> 21:58.000
[tires screeching]

21:58.083 --> 21:59.083
[Woman in Curlers]
We need to go right now!

21:59.166 --> 22:01.166
-We're all going to die!
-[alarms blaring]

22:01.250 --> 22:02.250
Daddy, I'm scared.

22:03.833 --> 22:05.166
-Come here.
-I'm scared.

22:05.250 --> 22:06.666
It's okay.
It's okay.

22:06.750 --> 22:13.375
♪ Make the world go away ♪

22:13.458 --> 22:19.750
♪ And get it off my shoulders ♪

22:20.666 --> 22:23.125
♪ Say the things you used to say ♪

22:23.208 --> 22:24.625
It's okay.

22:26.166 --> 22:27.541
It's okay.

22:27.625 --> 22:32.375
♪ And make the world go away ♪♪

22:35.583 --> 22:38.583
[♪ The Del-Vikings: "Come Go With Me"]

22:54.291 --> 22:57.625
We're blowing through our water reserves
at... at a troubling rate.

22:57.708 --> 22:59.458
Then we need to reallocate power

22:59.541 --> 23:02.958
to the temporary water filters
we built out of spare parts.

23:04.541 --> 23:05.875
Hey, guys.

23:07.083 --> 23:08.708
Can I help you, Reg?

23:08.791 --> 23:10.208
Have you seen Norm?

23:10.291 --> 23:14.583
Norm has been sent for a leadership
exchange program to Vault 31.

23:14.666 --> 23:17.000
-Everyone's moving up in the world but me.
-[object slams on table]

23:17.083 --> 23:21.875
Reg, this community has always done
what it takes to survive.

23:21.958 --> 23:24.083
[sputtering]
I guess so.

23:25.083 --> 23:28.291
-Whatcha guys working on?
-The water chip.

23:28.375 --> 23:31.416
Which we need to survive.
Which is broken.

23:31.500 --> 23:33.625
Oh, right, yeah, that.

23:33.708 --> 23:35.041
[clicking tongue, groaning]

23:35.791 --> 23:37.000
Let me know if I can help.

23:37.083 --> 23:40.708
I'm no engineer,
but you'd be surprised

23:40.791 --> 23:42.958
what a guy with a PhD
in Event Planning can...

23:43.041 --> 23:45.541
[device crashing,
glass shattering]

23:46.500 --> 23:48.791
Maybe you should find an outlet.

23:48.875 --> 23:50.708
-Start a club or something.
-[scoffs]

23:50.791 --> 23:52.083
A club?
[chuckles]

23:52.875 --> 23:54.000
What kind of club?

23:54.083 --> 23:55.958
We've been through a lot lately.

23:56.041 --> 23:58.208
Maybe you could start
a group for people

23:58.291 --> 24:02.500
to talk about any kind of feelings
you may be feeling.

24:02.583 --> 24:04.166
What kind of feelings am I feeling?

24:05.125 --> 24:07.791
Shame?
Uselessness?

24:07.875 --> 24:09.041
I don't feel useless.

24:10.166 --> 24:11.666
But I like shame.

24:12.833 --> 24:14.125
Shame, I can work with.

24:15.208 --> 24:18.083
There would need to be a snack budget,
of course.

24:18.166 --> 24:22.750
Send a supplies request, and I'll sign it.

24:26.916 --> 24:28.541
Heavy is the crown.

24:29.708 --> 24:31.458
You don't know the half of it.

24:31.541 --> 24:34.250
[Davey]
So, you see what I'm up against.

24:34.333 --> 24:37.625
In 33, I leave my quarters,
take a right turn,

24:37.708 --> 24:39.291
another right turn to the elevator.

24:39.375 --> 24:43.875
Here in 32, it's a left,
and a left to the elevator.

24:43.958 --> 24:47.666
Yup, again,
everything is the other way here,

24:47.750 --> 24:50.041
so just do the opposite
of what you used to do.

24:50.125 --> 24:53.166
-[terminal keys clacking]
-I'm not sure it's that simple.

24:53.250 --> 24:56.125
[sighs] It is.

24:56.208 --> 24:59.791
Now, look, as your Overseer,
I have to ask...

25:00.833 --> 25:04.666
is there anything
remotely actionable here?

25:04.750 --> 25:06.541
Something I can do for you?

25:07.791 --> 25:09.125
Signage.

25:09.875 --> 25:12.208
No, th-that could be controversial.

25:12.291 --> 25:15.500
Maybe you could commission
a feasibility study

25:15.583 --> 25:18.416
on the topic of signage.

25:20.625 --> 25:22.125
[laughing]

25:23.333 --> 25:25.333
[baby whining]

25:27.000 --> 25:28.833
Heck of a wife you got, Chet.

25:28.916 --> 25:30.458
We're not actually married.

25:30.541 --> 25:33.458
-And a beautiful baby.
-Not mine.

25:33.541 --> 25:36.750
I never had a family.
What happened?

25:36.833 --> 25:39.041
-Life, I guess.
-[baby whining]

25:39.125 --> 25:41.041
Things move quickly down here.

25:41.125 --> 25:43.458
I don't have a family either, Davey.

25:43.541 --> 25:45.166
Well, enjoy it.

25:47.875 --> 25:49.625
[Davey muttering] This way...

25:49.708 --> 25:51.708
[baby continues whining]

25:53.083 --> 25:55.083
[loud clacking]

25:55.166 --> 25:56.583
[baby whining]

25:58.083 --> 25:59.166
Oh, it's just you.

25:59.666 --> 26:00.833
Whew!

26:00.916 --> 26:03.833
That Davey, I mean...

26:03.916 --> 26:07.750
[chuckles]
Bless his heart, but, you know.

26:08.875 --> 26:10.875
[fruit squelching]

26:10.958 --> 26:14.083
Just seeing if you've gotten around
to giving me a job assignment yet.

26:14.166 --> 26:17.958
Just 'cause, you know,
everyone else has one.

26:18.041 --> 26:22.166
Uh, if you haven't chosen
a Gate-Keeper yet, I have experience.

26:22.916 --> 26:25.000
Chet, I've been busy.

26:25.083 --> 26:27.041
And I need someone
to take care of the baby,

26:27.125 --> 26:29.083
and it's used to you.

26:29.166 --> 26:33.250
But he is not my baby.

26:34.250 --> 26:37.041
[chuckles]
Everyone is acting like he is--

26:37.125 --> 26:38.375
Chet.

26:38.458 --> 26:40.625
Would you at least consider
giving him a name?

26:40.708 --> 26:43.875
Because the neighbors
have started to call him Chet Jr.

26:43.958 --> 26:45.541
Let's go with that then.

26:45.625 --> 26:49.625
Well, see, Chet Jr.
was my father's name.

26:49.708 --> 26:51.708
It's, uh, sort of a personal area for me,

26:51.791 --> 26:54.416
having watched him die of starvation
in the Weevil Famine.

26:54.500 --> 26:55.500
[knife thuds]

26:56.333 --> 27:00.166
Chet?
Are we having an argument?

27:04.041 --> 27:05.291
Chet Jr. it is.

27:06.333 --> 27:07.833
[chuckles]

27:13.125 --> 27:14.458
[Chet sighs]

27:14.541 --> 27:17.375
Oh, how are you with computers?

27:17.458 --> 27:19.958
Mm.
That was Norm's department.

27:20.041 --> 27:21.666
Maybe you can ask him
in the terminal.

27:22.333 --> 27:23.875
Great idea.

27:23.958 --> 27:26.916
I'll just send the other Vault
a message.

27:30.666 --> 27:32.666
[stroller wheels squeaking]

27:34.291 --> 27:35.583
[sighs]

27:37.708 --> 27:38.708
Okay.

27:39.583 --> 27:42.750
Okay.
[sighs deeply]

27:42.833 --> 27:44.833
[beeping]

27:47.500 --> 27:50.875
-[error notification]
-Cod ham cheese and rice!

27:51.125 --> 27:52.666
[Bud Askins/Brain-on-a-Roomba]
Oh, no, no, no, no!

27:52.750 --> 27:55.083
Inter-Vault Communications disabled?

27:55.166 --> 27:58.000
Alright, let's see. Where is he?

27:58.083 --> 27:59.416
Where is he? Where are you?!

27:59.500 --> 28:01.041
I'm coming for you.

28:01.125 --> 28:02.625
I'm coming for you!

28:03.083 --> 28:04.291
I'll be right there.

28:05.291 --> 28:07.666
Oh God, look at this mess!

28:07.750 --> 28:10.875
You really are a disgusting,
filthy animal, aren't you?

28:11.166 --> 28:13.375
Well I hope you aren't
expecting me to clean this up.

28:14.958 --> 28:17.000
-[water dripping]
-Hmm.

28:18.333 --> 28:20.750
So you found water,
but you're out of food.

28:20.833 --> 28:23.083
Starvation is a heck of a way
to kick the bucket.

28:24.875 --> 28:27.250
I'm offering you
a much more dignified solution

28:27.333 --> 28:30.416
to the one you've chosen for yourself,
son of Hank.

28:30.500 --> 28:32.541
Get in your dad's cryo pod.

28:33.541 --> 28:35.125
I'm not gonna be your prisoner.

28:35.208 --> 28:37.333
You're already my prisoner.

28:37.416 --> 28:41.875
All you have to do is wait
until the surface is safe to recolonize.

28:41.958 --> 28:44.458
Then, we'll all head up
for Reclamation Day.

28:45.125 --> 28:46.916
And when is that, exactly?

28:47.000 --> 28:49.583
When there's no one left on the surface
to disagree with us.

28:51.625 --> 28:53.208
Or you could just let me go home.

28:54.458 --> 28:56.625
People are gonna notice
I'm missing.

28:56.708 --> 28:58.291
Oh, we have a protocol for everything,

28:58.375 --> 29:00.708
including when someone
goes missing from a Vault.

29:00.791 --> 29:04.125
Your Overseer will handle it.
No one is comin' for you, buddy.

29:05.125 --> 29:08.541
Maybe you'll be more reasonable
once you're a little hungrier.

29:09.583 --> 29:12.458
Good luck finding something to eat
when you can't see.

29:15.750 --> 29:17.416
You're living in my world.

29:18.625 --> 29:22.791
These three Vaults are the product
of decades of strategizing.

29:22.875 --> 29:26.458
The combined efforts of hundreds
of the brightest pre-war minds

29:26.541 --> 29:29.583
with all the resources
of a functioning civilization.

29:29.666 --> 29:33.208
You're just some malcontent
who wandered down the wrong corridor.

29:34.541 --> 29:37.500
What hope do you have
against the greatest achievement

29:37.583 --> 29:39.958
in the history of Vertical Integration?

29:40.041 --> 29:42.000
Face it, son of Hank.

29:43.500 --> 29:44.875
You're in over your head.

29:45.958 --> 29:49.583
And no one is coming to save you.

30:01.125 --> 30:04.125
[suspenseful music playing]

30:16.000 --> 30:17.166
[music fades]

30:22.333 --> 30:24.166
-[Dogmeat panting]
-[insects chirping]

30:24.250 --> 30:26.333
[Lucy]
So, you think my dad

30:26.416 --> 30:28.541
is gonna lead you to your family.

30:28.625 --> 30:30.541
Which means you think
your family's still alive

30:30.625 --> 30:33.458
after 200 years, and somehow,
I'm the optimistic one?

30:40.041 --> 30:41.291
Your daddy.

30:42.416 --> 30:44.583
Always makin' new friends.

30:44.666 --> 30:46.875
[buzzing insects]

31:17.333 --> 31:20.083
[sighs]
She musta seen 'im pass by.

31:24.000 --> 31:26.250
W-We can just ask her.

31:28.291 --> 31:30.291
[Old Woman snoring]

31:33.041 --> 31:34.666
-'Scuse me!
-[snorting]

31:34.750 --> 31:35.958
Hi, there.

31:36.041 --> 31:38.583
I'd like one bowl of...

31:42.000 --> 31:43.208
flea soup.

31:44.541 --> 31:45.541
Sure.

31:50.458 --> 31:53.541
So, um, just wondering
if you happened to see...

31:58.958 --> 32:00.958
[liquid sloshing]

32:03.625 --> 32:06.625
I got some crackers
if you want 'em.

32:06.708 --> 32:08.416
They're in my other pants.

32:09.250 --> 32:11.791
Oh, uh, I'm okay, but...

32:11.875 --> 32:13.875
Eat it while it's hot, Miss.

32:17.916 --> 32:19.666
[sniffing]

32:20.833 --> 32:22.041
Mm!

32:22.875 --> 32:24.375
[bowl clattering]

32:25.375 --> 32:26.666
Yeah.
[clearing throat]

32:26.750 --> 32:30.291
So, have you happened to have seen
a... a man passing by

32:30.375 --> 32:34.541
in a sort of oversized outfit
made of metal?

32:34.625 --> 32:36.166
He took my son.

32:36.250 --> 32:38.416
Oh.
I'm sure your son is, um--

32:38.500 --> 32:39.875
He's dead.

32:39.958 --> 32:41.750
No, we don't know that.

32:41.833 --> 32:42.833
[Old Woman]
No.

32:42.916 --> 32:44.458
He's dead.

32:44.541 --> 32:46.000
Just my kind of luck.

32:47.500 --> 32:49.250
Cocksucker owed me money.

32:52.333 --> 32:55.958
-I'm sorry for... money.
-Mm.

32:56.041 --> 32:57.625
He went that way.

32:58.375 --> 32:59.458
[Lucy] Thank you.

33:03.333 --> 33:07.000
[Old Woman] You find any money
on the body, it's mine!

33:11.750 --> 33:13.916
[Ghoul] Question.
What exactly is it

33:14.000 --> 33:16.083
you plan on doin'
once we find your daddy?

33:17.083 --> 33:19.083
We gonna do it like usual?

33:19.166 --> 33:21.208
You put a bullet in his ass,

33:21.291 --> 33:23.291
leave it to me to put one
in his head?

33:25.833 --> 33:26.958
No, I'm...

33:28.000 --> 33:30.416
-gonna bring him to justice.
-[chuckles]

33:30.500 --> 33:33.166
-[Dogmeat barking]
-You think he deserves that?

33:33.250 --> 33:35.708
[Lucy] I was raised to believe
that's what everyone deserves,

33:35.791 --> 33:38.500
so people know that
how they conduct themselves matters,

33:38.583 --> 33:40.041
and they don't give up hope.

33:40.125 --> 33:44.208
Like you say you did
but, really, it's still in there.

33:46.833 --> 33:49.416
Well, I hate to break it to you, darlin',

33:49.500 --> 33:51.541
but the way you was raised
wasn't real.

33:53.041 --> 33:56.208
I know that.
But look at your alternative.

33:58.708 --> 34:00.583
Guess I'm just trying
to lead by example.

34:07.875 --> 34:10.875
-[outlaw country music playing]
-[Dogmeat barking]

34:17.166 --> 34:18.708
[Dogmeat panting]

34:26.583 --> 34:29.250
[tense music playing]

34:29.333 --> 34:31.333
[Dogmeat barking]

34:46.208 --> 34:48.208
[moles laughing]

34:50.166 --> 34:51.791
[Cooper]
They sat around that table

34:51.875 --> 34:53.708
and they talked about
the ending of the world

34:53.791 --> 34:56.666
like they were talking
about a new business strategy.

34:56.750 --> 34:58.875
[Kate Williams] Sounds like you heard
something interesting.

35:00.583 --> 35:01.916
What, you knew?

35:03.250 --> 35:06.916
And now, you do, too,
so what are we gonna do about it?

35:07.916 --> 35:09.916
What do you mean,
"What are we gonna do about it?"

35:10.000 --> 35:12.083
I told you.
I'm not a spy.

35:12.166 --> 35:14.666
I'm not a red.
I'm a fuckin' Hollywood actor

35:14.750 --> 35:17.041
who likes horses and cars.

35:17.125 --> 35:19.750
[Kate] And you also
happen to be famous.

35:19.833 --> 35:23.083
And fame is a rare kind of power.

35:23.166 --> 35:26.750
You get to sit in rooms that I can't,
meet people that I could never--

35:26.833 --> 35:28.333
Meet... meet people like who?

35:30.500 --> 35:32.500
Are you familiar
with Robert House?

35:34.500 --> 35:37.541
Yeah, I'm familiar with Robert House.

35:37.625 --> 35:39.375
The guy owns half
of Las Vegas.

35:39.458 --> 35:43.583
He's also building a privately owned
missile system in Las Vegas...

35:44.625 --> 35:49.250
with enough firepower to follow through
on your wife's proposals.

35:50.916 --> 35:54.125
When the bombs drop,
it'll be Robert House

35:54.208 --> 35:56.250
that presses the button.

35:58.250 --> 36:02.000
Are you asking me to spy
on the wealthiest man in America?

36:03.625 --> 36:04.916
Not spy on him.

36:11.708 --> 36:15.000
-You want me to--
-Your wife is going to Vegas next week

36:16.125 --> 36:19.333
to sell Cold Fusion
to Robert House.

36:19.416 --> 36:22.625
-[scoffs]
-Then, he'll have everything he needs

36:22.708 --> 36:23.875
to press that button

36:23.958 --> 36:25.625
-unless you stop him.
-[sighs]

36:25.708 --> 36:29.791
Play nice with your wife
and get on that trip to Vegas.

36:33.833 --> 36:35.208
Where are you going?

36:35.291 --> 36:38.375
Home, while I still have one.

36:38.458 --> 36:41.041
When the world
goes down in flames,

36:41.125 --> 36:43.333
at least you'll know
your hands are clean.

36:51.833 --> 36:54.208
[Cooper] [sighs]
Janey, let's go.

36:54.291 --> 36:55.291
Come on. Come on.

36:55.375 --> 36:56.375
-[Janey] What?
-Come on.

36:56.458 --> 36:57.500
[mallet thumping]

36:57.583 --> 36:59.958
[mole laughing]

37:01.000 --> 37:04.625
[announcer] [on radio] In business news,
West Tek stocks are up again amid reports

37:04.708 --> 37:06.625
-their latest biological products...
-[chopping]

37:06.708 --> 37:08.916
...will revolutionize skincare.

37:09.000 --> 37:11.333
Meanwhile, RobCo owner
Robert House

37:11.416 --> 37:14.750
created a stir today
with remarks on the escalating war.

37:14.833 --> 37:18.125
In an interview with Galaxy News,
he stated that the question

37:18.208 --> 37:20.791
might not be whether the world will end,

37:20.875 --> 37:24.166
but merely who
will push the button.

37:24.250 --> 37:27.000
More on that story after a word
from our sponsors.

37:27.083 --> 37:28.291
[door unlocking]

37:33.541 --> 37:35.791
[woman] [on radio]
Yum Yum Deviled Eggs!

37:43.333 --> 37:46.333
[tense music playing]

37:48.708 --> 37:50.708
[footsteps approaching]

37:57.583 --> 37:58.916
[sighs]

38:01.541 --> 38:02.791
Welcome home.

38:02.875 --> 38:05.541
[music swells]

38:18.791 --> 38:20.958
Looks like Daddy
took a detour.

38:25.458 --> 38:27.583
Never seen a Vault
like this before.

38:31.666 --> 38:33.875
Par for the course,
in my experience.

38:35.333 --> 38:36.916
You've been to a lot of Vaults?

38:38.375 --> 38:39.541
Uh-huh.

38:40.291 --> 38:41.833
[Lucy] Oh.

38:42.750 --> 38:43.916
You must like 'em.

38:47.666 --> 38:51.958
Every time I step foot
in one of these concrete shoeboxes...

38:53.250 --> 38:55.458
I gotta make peace with the fact
that I might finally learn

38:55.541 --> 38:59.541
what happened
to my wife and my daughter.

39:01.250 --> 39:04.458
Whether they be alive, dead, or...

39:06.166 --> 39:07.708
something far worse.

39:10.333 --> 39:11.375
Right.

39:13.208 --> 39:14.458
I know about the experiments.

39:15.708 --> 39:16.708
I've been to Vault 4.

39:18.375 --> 39:21.250
[Ghoul]
Vault 4 is the best-case scenario.

39:21.333 --> 39:24.125
Well, to be fair, it was a little weirder
than the one I came from.

39:27.541 --> 39:29.333
You think so?

39:29.416 --> 39:32.208
How many towns
did they destroy down in Vault 4?

39:37.458 --> 39:39.000
-Open it.
-[grunting]

39:41.291 --> 39:42.291
[scoffs]

39:45.041 --> 39:47.083
[elevator doors whirring]

39:54.208 --> 39:56.375
You really think
my dad is down there?

39:56.458 --> 39:58.041
The trail has him comin' in.

39:59.541 --> 40:01.083
Trail has him goin' out, too.

40:07.416 --> 40:08.958
But what I'm curious about...

40:10.791 --> 40:12.625
is why he even came at all.

40:14.458 --> 40:15.458
[Ghoul sighs]

40:21.583 --> 40:23.375
Ain't you a little curious, too?

40:28.125 --> 40:31.125
[tense music playing]

40:41.208 --> 40:43.250
[waves crashing]

40:48.291 --> 40:50.833
[Reg] It's not your fault
you were born in a Vault.

40:51.750 --> 40:52.916
Let me hear you say it.

40:53.000 --> 40:55.833
[group] It's not my fault
I was born in a Vault.

40:55.916 --> 40:59.041
And it's not your fault that your parents
were or are related.

40:59.125 --> 41:00.958
And it's not my fault my parents...

41:01.041 --> 41:03.625
-[Marianne] ...were related.
-[both] ...were or are related.

41:08.166 --> 41:10.083
Feels good to say it out loud,
doesn't it?

41:11.916 --> 41:13.583
That's just the first step.

41:13.666 --> 41:17.208
Trust me, as someone who's come out
on the other side of this,

41:17.291 --> 41:19.041
I know what it's like
to wonder if people

41:19.125 --> 41:22.083
look down their noses at you
based on your family tree.

41:22.166 --> 41:24.166
A regular person
can have an ingrown toenail,

41:24.250 --> 41:27.583
and it's just an ingrown toenail.

41:27.666 --> 41:28.916
But we?

41:30.833 --> 41:34.250
We have to wonder if it's because
our genes are somehow broken.

41:35.416 --> 41:37.375
If I am somehow broken.

41:39.333 --> 41:43.041
So, we're gonna change the rules, right?

41:44.375 --> 41:45.416
Hm?

41:45.500 --> 41:46.875
[Horny Red-Haired Guy]
No inbreeding in the Vault.

41:46.958 --> 41:48.333
We're gonna change that, right?

41:49.416 --> 41:52.166
No.
That... That's not what this is about.

41:52.250 --> 41:54.958
The rules are good.
But that doesn't mean those of us

41:55.041 --> 41:57.208
who are products of inbreeding
need to feel bad.

41:57.291 --> 41:58.500
You understand?

41:59.625 --> 42:00.666
Come on.

42:06.166 --> 42:08.250
[crunching]

42:09.250 --> 42:11.375
-I have a question.
-Uh, yes, Marianne.

42:11.458 --> 42:14.000
-I have a mild allergy to dust.
-Mm.

42:14.083 --> 42:17.500
And sometimes I wonder
if it was my father's fault

42:17.583 --> 42:21.208
because he fell in love
with his cousin... my mother.

42:21.291 --> 42:24.750
I just wonder
if there's a biological connection.

42:24.833 --> 42:26.375
[crunching loudly]

42:26.458 --> 42:29.166
I didn't study genetics, so...

42:29.250 --> 42:30.416
Oh, well, okay.

42:30.500 --> 42:32.750
It certainly could be his fault.

42:33.500 --> 42:36.375
I knew it!
Great snacks, by the way.

42:36.458 --> 42:38.291
[♪ The Ink Spots:
"It's All Over but the Crying"]

42:38.375 --> 42:40.500
You know, I always felt my mother
viewed me as a rival,

42:40.583 --> 42:43.125
which mirrored her relationship
with her own mother,

42:43.208 --> 42:46.041
who was in love with my father,
her fifth cousin.

42:46.125 --> 42:48.833
All the fifth cousins were fourth cousins
to the second cousins.

42:48.916 --> 42:50.291
[crunching loudly]
I mean, it's not exactly...

42:50.375 --> 42:53.291
-[voice fading]
-♪ It's all over ♪

42:53.375 --> 42:58.375
♪ But the crying ♪

42:58.458 --> 43:00.333
[Bud Askins/Brain-on-a-Roomba]
[sighs] It won't be long now.

43:00.416 --> 43:04.291
♪ And nobody's crying ♪

43:04.375 --> 43:06.000
[Bud Askins/Brain-on-a-Roomba]
You must be so hungry

43:06.083 --> 43:07.333
and so thirsty.

43:08.458 --> 43:11.583
Why torture yourself
when there's a nice, cozy cryo pod

43:11.666 --> 43:13.916
just waitin' for you to hop into?

43:14.000 --> 43:17.000
-♪ Friends all over ♪♪
-What was my dad like?

43:17.083 --> 43:18.208
[music stops]

43:18.666 --> 43:19.875
[Bud Askins/Brain-on-a-Roomba]
Ambitious.

43:21.583 --> 43:23.041
Then why was he here?

43:23.125 --> 43:24.750
[Bud Askins/Brain-on-a-Roomba]
Well, being one of Bud's Buds

43:24.875 --> 43:26.416
was a highly coveted position
back in the day.

43:26.500 --> 43:27.750
[insect skittering]

43:27.833 --> 43:29.541
We had applicants from
as far out as Fresno.

43:30.583 --> 43:33.958
Mmm. Eating that might seem like
a good idea, but it's toxic.

43:34.041 --> 43:36.291
You'll die a slow, painful death.

43:37.208 --> 43:39.625
If you aren't willing to go into cryo,
you could always let me inject you

43:39.708 --> 43:41.166
-with this guy right here.
-[whirring]

43:41.750 --> 43:45.166
It really would be a whole lot easier.
For both of us.

43:46.833 --> 43:50.666
-What does it do?
-It kills you, quick and painless.

43:50.750 --> 43:53.916
Your body will rapidly decompose,
turning into a dust

43:54.000 --> 43:56.208
that will get circulated
through the ventilation system,

43:56.291 --> 43:58.750
ultimately making its way
into your cornfields back home.

43:58.833 --> 44:01.208
Not so bad, if you think about it.

44:01.291 --> 44:05.250
Then, you won't have to deal
with all the headaches of being alive.

44:06.458 --> 44:09.916
So, you have two rational choices.

44:10.000 --> 44:12.708
Get in your dad's pod.
Or die.

44:14.750 --> 44:17.333
You're right,
I only have two rational choices.

44:19.375 --> 44:20.958
[whirring]

44:22.083 --> 44:23.791
But plenty of irrational ones.

44:25.500 --> 44:26.833
What are you doing?

44:27.833 --> 44:30.791
Two hundred years of planning
in order for everything to go just right.

44:30.875 --> 44:33.125
That seems like a lot of work,
if you ask me.

44:33.208 --> 44:35.083
Stay back.
Stay back.

44:35.375 --> 44:36.375
Aah!

44:36.458 --> 44:38.750
I think plans are slightly overrated,
personally.

44:41.041 --> 44:43.291
No, no, no, no.
Wait, I need that to threaten you.

44:43.375 --> 44:45.375
-What are you doing?
-Thawing everyone.

44:45.458 --> 44:48.708
What? No!
You can't just thaw them all.

44:48.791 --> 44:50.791
-[buzzer blaring]
-[air hissing]

44:52.041 --> 44:55.250
No, no, no. They're supposed to come out
once every 30 years.

44:55.333 --> 44:57.375
This isn't even a cogent plan.
It's just chaos.

44:57.833 --> 44:59.666
Agreed.
Plans are hard.

45:00.541 --> 45:03.500
Chaos, though...
chaos is easy.

45:05.583 --> 45:08.583
[dramatic music playing]

45:17.708 --> 45:19.708
[elevator doors whirring]

45:25.708 --> 45:27.708
[spurs jingling lightly]

45:45.416 --> 45:47.625
[Ghoul]
More matching jackets.

45:53.833 --> 45:56.583
Why would Vault-Tec allow Communists
in one of their Vaults?

45:57.875 --> 45:59.916
I wouldn't be so sure they did.

46:11.166 --> 46:14.291
[man speaking Mandarin on TV]

46:14.375 --> 46:17.541
[English narrator]
Individual is secondary to the collective.

46:18.916 --> 46:22.041
[man speaking Mandarin]

46:23.750 --> 46:28.333
[English narrator] ...true comrade
chooses cooperation over individualism.

46:28.416 --> 46:29.958
[music in Mandarin playing]

46:30.041 --> 46:32.791
[man speaking Mandarin]

46:34.166 --> 46:37.375
[English narrator] Our enemy
has chosen the interest of product

46:37.458 --> 46:39.875
over the interest of people.

46:39.958 --> 46:43.416
We choose people over product.

46:47.625 --> 46:50.666
[narration continues]

46:53.500 --> 46:55.125
These are Americans.

46:56.625 --> 46:58.625
The Vault turned them
into Communists.

46:58.708 --> 47:01.000
[English narrator]
Freedom is inevitable.

47:02.416 --> 47:05.416
[music in Mandarin continues]

47:10.250 --> 47:14.416
[English narrator]
The revolution will not be futile.

47:19.208 --> 47:21.083
[terminal keys clicking]

47:24.916 --> 47:27.041
[man speaking Mandarin]

47:27.125 --> 47:30.583
[English narrator] The individual
is secondary to the collective.

47:32.000 --> 47:33.708
[terminal keys clicking]

47:35.125 --> 47:37.125
[terminal chirping]

47:38.083 --> 47:39.708
[Lucy]
My dad removed the drive.

47:41.875 --> 47:43.125
[footstep squishing]

48:27.583 --> 48:29.583
[metal squeaking loudly]

48:41.125 --> 48:42.833
Well hello there, Sugarbomb!

48:47.375 --> 48:50.208
Looks like your daddy
picked himself up a guinea pig.

48:55.125 --> 48:56.958
What do you want?

48:59.000 --> 49:00.000
I...

49:01.208 --> 49:03.916
fix... everything.

49:04.875 --> 49:07.375
Go home...

49:08.708 --> 49:09.833
Sugarbomb.

49:11.166 --> 49:12.375
Go home!

49:14.250 --> 49:15.250
Go home!

49:17.416 --> 49:18.500
Go!

49:20.833 --> 49:23.500
[screaming] Ho-a-a-a!

49:24.750 --> 49:26.750
[flesh splattering]

49:35.000 --> 49:36.916
[gasping]

49:40.625 --> 49:42.625
[Lucy breathing shakily]

49:50.958 --> 49:53.625
You ever seen your daddy
use one of these before?

49:55.166 --> 49:56.250
No.

49:58.625 --> 50:00.375
You gonna take his advice?

50:03.916 --> 50:06.291
He won't stop hurting people.

50:07.041 --> 50:08.833
Yeah, no shit.

50:10.166 --> 50:11.333
[Ghoul sighs]

50:12.291 --> 50:14.208
Well, then we better get going.

50:18.708 --> 50:20.416
[sighs]

50:22.333 --> 50:23.333
[Black Box thuds]

50:33.208 --> 50:36.041
[heavy footsteps]

50:36.125 --> 50:37.625
[horn blares]

50:37.708 --> 50:39.708
[heavy footsteps continue]

50:42.500 --> 50:45.500
[dramatic music playing]

51:24.500 --> 51:26.500
[sighs deeply]

51:37.916 --> 51:39.916
[terminal powering up]

51:40.000 --> 51:41.250
[terminal] You have...

51:42.416 --> 51:47.916
-[beep]
-...462,311 unread messages.

51:49.166 --> 51:50.583
Let's get to it.

51:50.666 --> 51:52.625
[♪ Roy Orbison: "Working for the Man"]

51:52.708 --> 51:55.833
♪ Hey now,
you better listen to me ♪

51:55.916 --> 51:58.041
-♪ Every one of you ♪
-♪ Ooh! ♪

51:58.125 --> 52:01.250
♪ We've got a lotta, lotta,
lotta, lotta work to do ♪

52:01.333 --> 52:02.541
[inhaling deeply]
Mm!

52:02.625 --> 52:06.916
♪ Forget about your women
and that water can ♪

52:07.000 --> 52:08.208
-♪ Ooh! ♪
-[sighs]

52:08.291 --> 52:12.750
♪ Today you're working
for the man ♪

52:12.833 --> 52:15.750
♪ Oh, oh, oh, oh, oh ♪

52:15.833 --> 52:19.375
-♪ Ooh! Ooh! ♪
-♪ Oh, oh, oh ♪

52:19.458 --> 52:22.250
♪ Well, pick up your feet,
we've got a deadline to meet ♪

52:22.333 --> 52:25.208
♪ I'm gonna see you
make it on time ♪

52:25.291 --> 52:28.291
♪ Oh, don't relax,
I want elbows and backs ♪

52:28.375 --> 52:31.666
♪ I wanna see everybody
from behind ♪

52:31.750 --> 52:35.875
-♪ Ooh! ♪
-♪ 'Cause you're working for the man ♪

52:35.958 --> 52:38.208
♪ Working for the man ♪

52:38.291 --> 52:41.916
♪ You gotta make him a hand ♪

52:42.000 --> 52:44.375
♪ Working for the man ♪

52:45.833 --> 52:50.416
♪ Ooh! Ooh! Ooh! ♪

52:50.500 --> 52:51.625
♪ Ooh! ♪♪

52:52.750 --> 52:55.750
[eerie music playing]

53:01.041 --> 53:02.291
[beeps]

53:06.916 --> 53:09.458
-[button clicking]
-[light radio static]

53:09.541 --> 53:11.000
-[sighs]
-[static warbling]

53:20.291 --> 53:23.458
This is Hank MacLean,
reporting for duty, sir.

53:26.375 --> 53:28.875
Nobody in Vault-Tec
knows I'm here.

53:31.291 --> 53:33.916
And nobody in Vault-Tec
knows much of anything anymore.

53:36.958 --> 53:38.833
Wanted to let you know
I'm still alive.

53:40.750 --> 53:42.708
I hope you are, too.

53:42.791 --> 53:45.958
I mean, I don't doubt that you are.

53:46.041 --> 53:47.625
You spent so much time...

53:48.708 --> 53:51.750
calculating how to survive
all possible contingencies.

53:55.500 --> 53:57.666
Uh, I've been keeping busy.

53:57.750 --> 53:59.833
I'm in Vegas these days,

53:59.916 --> 54:02.125
back in your old
stomping grounds, actually...

54:03.125 --> 54:05.458
trying to pick up
where you all left off.

54:08.083 --> 54:10.208
Looks like a couple
of the Vault experiments

54:10.291 --> 54:11.875
ran into some speed bumps.

54:13.541 --> 54:17.208
24 made progress
on the brain-computer interface.

54:19.583 --> 54:22.958
This one, miniaturization.

54:26.416 --> 54:28.208
What it all needs is integrating.

54:29.208 --> 54:31.625
But I'm confident
that if I just roll up my sleeves,

54:31.708 --> 54:33.541
I can bring it all home for you.

54:35.250 --> 54:38.083
Then, we can finally talk
about my promotion.

54:40.291 --> 54:41.541
[blows sharply]

54:44.166 --> 54:46.458
I'm gonna complete
the work you started.

54:47.500 --> 54:51.250
And when this is all over,
you will be begging me to help you.

54:55.208 --> 54:57.375
-[button clicking]
-♪ 'Cause the company ♪

54:57.458 --> 54:59.208
♪ And the daughter you see ♪

54:59.291 --> 55:02.500
♪ They're both gonna be all mine ♪

55:02.583 --> 55:06.208
-♪ Ooh! ♪
-♪ Yeah, I'm gonna be the man ♪

55:06.291 --> 55:09.125
♪ I'm gonna be the man ♪

55:09.208 --> 55:12.291
♪ Gotta make him a hand ♪

55:12.375 --> 55:15.125
♪ If I'm gonna be the man ♪

55:16.666 --> 55:19.166
♪ Ooh! Ooh! ♪

55:19.250 --> 55:22.166
♪ So, I'm picking 'em up
and I'm laying 'em down ♪

55:22.250 --> 55:25.583
♪ I believe he's gonna work me
into the ground ♪

55:25.666 --> 55:28.416
♪ I pull to the left,
I heave to the right ♪

55:28.500 --> 55:32.000
♪ I oughta kill him,
but it wouldn't be right ♪

55:32.083 --> 55:35.791
-♪ Ooh! ♪
-♪ 'Cause I'm working for the man ♪

55:35.875 --> 55:38.416
♪ Working for the man ♪

55:38.500 --> 55:41.916
♪ I gotta make him a hand ♪

55:42.000 --> 55:45.000
♪ Working for the man ♪

55:45.083 --> 55:48.750
-♪ Oh, oh, oh, oh, oh ♪
-♪ Ooh! ♪

55:48.833 --> 55:51.500
-♪ Oh, oh, oh ♪
-♪ Ooh! ♪

55:51.583 --> 55:55.041
♪ Well, the boss man's daughter
sneaks me water ♪

55:55.125 --> 55:57.666
♪ Every time
her daddy's down the line ♪

55:57.750 --> 56:01.041
♪ She says, meet me tonight,
love a me right ♪

56:01.125 --> 56:03.875
♪ And everything is gonna be fine ♪

56:03.958 --> 56:07.333
♪ So, I slave all day
without much pay ♪

56:07.416 --> 56:10.000
♪ But I'm just biding my time ♪

56:10.083 --> 56:13.416
♪ 'Cause the company
and the daughter, you see ♪

56:13.500 --> 56:16.916
♪ They're both gonna be all mine ♪

56:17.000 --> 56:18.083
♪ Ooh! ♪♪

56:18.166 --> 56:21.166
[tense music playing]

56:22.750 --> 56:24.083
[Quintus]
Together...

56:25.208 --> 56:27.416
we will fulfill our promise.

56:30.541 --> 56:33.375
To make better this fallen world.

56:35.416 --> 56:36.666
[Paladin Xander Harkness]
Sorry to interrupt.

56:39.166 --> 56:42.166
I understand we're discussing
a civil war.

56:42.250 --> 56:44.791
♪♪

56:46.208 --> 56:47.833
The Commonwealth
are gonna kill us all.

56:47.916 --> 56:49.083
Unless I can stop it.

56:50.583 --> 56:51.875
What do we always say?

56:51.958 --> 56:55.000
[all]
Most kids are dead by this age!

56:57.875 --> 56:59.625
[Lucy]
I'm looking for someone.

56:59.708 --> 57:01.625
[Rodriguez] What do you plan to do
to him when you find him?

57:01.708 --> 57:03.666
What say you, Miss MacLean?

57:05.541 --> 57:08.083
[Lucy] Your family may
very well still be out there.

57:08.166 --> 57:09.958
But one thing I wouldn't count on

57:10.041 --> 57:12.041
is them appreciating the kind of person
you've become.

57:12.125 --> 57:14.125
♪♪

57:18.416 --> 57:21.000
[Barb] There are worse people
out there than me.

57:23.916 --> 57:26.083
[Securitron] Don't you know what
they say in Vegas?

57:26.750 --> 57:30.041
Everyone's a winner!
Eventually.

57:30.625 --> 57:33.166
[Ghoul] Same goes for losing,
in my experience.

57:33.250 --> 57:35.083
Except for one man.

57:39.291 --> 57:40.666
[stranger] Mr. Howard.

57:41.666 --> 57:44.666
I know that you came to Vegas
to kill me.

57:47.000 --> 57:48.375
Did you not?

57:50.875 --> 57:54.041
And I don't know yet how you
play a part in ending the world.

57:54.125 --> 57:56.291
But you most certainly do.

57:59.750 --> 58:03.625
[Betty] If you don't help us,
there won't be a Vault 33 anymore.

58:05.000 --> 58:06.291
[Norm]
Dad, if you can hear me...

58:07.000 --> 58:08.375
what's gonna happen to our Vault?

58:08.458 --> 58:10.333
♪♪

58:26.916 --> 58:28.458
[Hank]
My little Sugarbomb.

58:32.458 --> 58:35.458
♪♪
